From Anthony Thyssen Subject COLORS and X windows AIcons Extract from the color README file for Anthony's Icon For Network Color I tried to start a discussion in ' at the start of the year about some sort of standard color table' that icons should follow say to colors including colors for a small grey scale but no one responded at The problem is that if the colors for icons are just used willy nilly you will soon find that the workstations color table devotes itself solely the window manager icons and other adminstrative tasks' instead of applications that actually require the colors for proper Color needful applications'' such as Picture and graphic displayers Animation Real Time video Raytracers The following is a suggested color table for icons and general Icons Window Managers and general applications should follow this table or something like it UNLESS the application is color needful'' for each primary color red green blue three colors EG values and This results in colors representing most of the standard colors for use in two extra shades of grey EG vales black and white red other colors probably of some primary color to provide shading a and D look to buttons and titlebars in the window This table represents colors and represents a large range of posibilities for the above administrative services'' of the Anthony Thyssen SysProg Griffith University A Gods idea of amusement is a Snakes Ladders game with greased Terry Pratchett Wyrd Sisters